  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Exploring Notifications Integration**\n\nI\'m now delving into the implementation of a push notification system within this Permit to Work web application. I\'m focusing on user notifications and real-time updates within the EHS workflows. My aim is to integrate a functional, either simulated or actual, push notification capability to enhance the application\'s usability.\n\n\n**Designing Push Notifications**\n\nI\'m presently designing a two-tiered push notification system. Firstly, I plan to leverage the native `Notification` API for device-level alerts when permits require user action. A dedicated `pushNotificationService.ts` will handle permissions, subscriptions, and notification delivery, including UI elements for subscription management. Secondly, I\'m developing an in-app simulator, probably as an overlay or banner, for use within the application\'s iframe preview environment.\n\n\n**Implementing Fallback Notifications**\n\nI\'m now implementing a crucial fallback mechanism for push notifications. Recognizing potential restrictions within iframes, I\'m designing a sophisticated, visually identical in-app banner. It\'ll replicate the look and feel of a native notification, complete with sound, vibration, and click-to-action functionality. I\'m focusing on ensuring this alternative provides the same real-time feedback and user experience as direct browser notifications. Specifically, I\'m designing the UI and event triggers to react exactly as described.\n\n\n**Refining Notification Triggers**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the precise triggers for these notifications. My focus is on ensuring they\'re tied directly to key permit state changes within the application. Specifically, I\'m examining `App.tsx` and related modules, noting that updates, creations, and potentially other actions need to be tracked. The goal is to accurately detect when notifications are sent to the correct users, with details about the permits (ID, title, action). I\'m looking at implementing a stunning styled card with a click action to immediately put users into the action state with the permits.\n\n\n"
