  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Updating Permit Detail Handlers**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the `src/components/PermitDetail.tsx` file and updating the handler functions there. Specifically, I\'m working on refactoring `handleSubmitDraft`, `handleProductionAction`, `handleElectricalAction`, `handlePerformGasTest`, `handleHseAction`, `handleRequestClosure`, and `handleSupervisorVerify`, to ensure they align with the current best practices.\n\n\n**Revising Notification Logic**\n\nI\'m now revising the notification logic within the `PermitDetail.tsx` handler block. The goal is to incorporate `PushNotificationService.sendNotification` into `handleSubmitDraft` as well as others, ensuring the English and Arabic messages are professional, informative, and tailored. I\'m focusing on crafting the precise notification dispatch for each handler, starting with `handleSubmitDraft`. I\'ll be meticulously checking this logic.\n\n\n**Implementing Notification Triggers**\n\nI\'ve just added notification dispatch logic within the `handleSubmitDraft` function for when a permit is submitted. I\'m dynamically determining the next permit status, whether it\'s pending department review or directly to HSE. The notification content is language-aware, with separate English and Arabic messages, tailored to the recipient\'s role (PRODUCTION, ELECTRICAL, or HSE). I\'m also ensuring the notification includes relevant information like the permit ID and title, alongside the specific action required.\n\n\n**Refining Handler Logic**\n\nI\'m now refining the `handleProductionAction` function. I\'ve integrated checks for comments. The core logic now dynamically alters the permit status based on whether the electrical clearance is required and approved or not. I\'ve incorporated the logic from the comments as well, including checks for required electrical approvals.\n\n\n**Integrating Electrical Notification**\n\nI\'m currently integrating the electrical notification logic within `handleProductionAction`, as the electrical clearance approval determines the next permit status. Depending on approvals, I\'m now sending notifications to electrical or HSE, ensuring the notification content correctly aligns with the status. I\'ve accounted for electrical department needs.\n\n\n**Finalizing Production Approval**\n\nI\'ve just finalized the `handleProductionAction` logic. Now, based on the approval status and comments provided, I determine the next permit status. I\'m also ensuring the appropriate notifications are sent. Rejection triggers a notification to the requester with the reason; approval triggers an HSE notification for on-site checks. I\'m satisfied that this section is thoroughly complete, and now I\'ll prepare for the next handler.\n\n\n**Addressing Electrical Action**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `handleElectricalAction` handler function to manage electrical approvals, including checks for production approvals and LOTO requirements, and sending an alert if the required clearances are not provided. The function will also manage the LOTO inputs. I\'m focusing on ensuring approvals, based on the `approve` boolean, appropriately update permit statuses and trigger necessary notifications.\n\n\n**Implementing LOTO Approval**\n\nI\'m currently implementing LOTO approvals within the `handleElectricalAction` handler. If the electrical department approves, I determine the next status, transitioning to either HSE review or pending department review if production is still required. I\'m dynamically sending notifications based on the outcome of the electrical action. I\'m focusing on language-aware messages, ensuring relevant details are included.\n\n\n**Integrating LOTO Implementation**\n\nI\'m now integrating the LOTO implementation within the `handleElectricalAction` handler. If the electrical department approves, I transition the status to HSE review. The language-aware notifications are dispatched for approvals, making sure all information is included for production team members. I\'m focusing on language-aware messages, and ensuring relevant details are included.\n\n\n\n**Refining LOTO Rejection**\n\nI\'m finalizing the LOTO rejection within the `handleElectricalAction` handler, implementing appropriate notifications to the requester if a LOTO request is rejected. I\'ve tailored the messages and included the rejection reason. I\'m focusing on language-aware messages, ensuring relevant details are included in the electrical action.\n\n\n\n**Evaluating Gas Test Results**\n\nI\'m now evaluating the `handlePerformGasTest` function. I\'ve focused on implementing the gas test result logic, determining pass/fail based on oxygen, LEL, and CO readings. I\'ve crafted the Arabic and English audit log entries and notifications to communicate test outcomes clearly.\n\n\n**Assessing Gas Test Notifications**\n\nI\'m now assessing the notification for gas test outcomes within the `handlePerformGasTest` function. I\'m focusing on the clarity and accuracy of the notifications, with language-specific messages. I\'m dynamically generating the content based on whether the test passed or failed, including oxygen, LEL, and CO readings for HSE review. I\'m ensuring both Arabic and English versions are informative and professional.\n\n\n**Evaluating HSE Action**\n\nI\'m now evaluating the `handleHseAction` handler for final HSE action, either approval or rejection of the permit. I\'m focusing on checks, the language-aware notifications to ensure alignment with gas testing requirements, and clear communication of any safety directions or the absence of comments. If the gas test isn\'t passed and requires it, the process stops.\n\n\n**Finalizing HSE Approval**\n\nI\'m now finalizing the HSE approval logic within `handleHseAction`, making sure that I have implemented checks for gas testing and LOTO requirements to trigger safety direction and notifications for the requester. I\'m focusing on ensuring clear and professional language-aware notifications are dispatched for approvals, rejections, and any related safety directions.\n\n\n**Finalizing Rejection Updates**\n\nI\'m now finalizing the `handleHseAction` handler, implementing clear notifications to the requester for rejected permits, including the rejection reason and any necessary safety directions. I\'ve tailored the language-aware messages. The appropriate status updates have been configured, and I am ensuring the audit trail accurately reflects this activity.\n\n\n**Implementing Closure Requests**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `handleRequestClosure` function. I\'ve integrated a check for the presence of comments. I send an alert if comments are missing. If comments are present, I create an audit entry and then notify HSE that a closure request has been submitted. I\'m focusing on the clarity and completeness of the notifications, in both Arabic and English.\n\n\n**Refining Closure Notifications**\n\nI\'m now refining the `handleSupervisorVerify` handler function. I\'ve implemented logic to prevent verification if the gas test isn\'t passed and integrated a check for comments. I am sending an alert if the comments are missing. If they are present, I now update the permit status to pending closure. I\'m focusing on crafting language-aware notifications and ensuring that the audit trail reflects the closure action.\n\n\n**Finalizing Active Permit Release**\n\nI\'m now implementing the final logic for `handleSupervisorVerify`, dispatching notifications to the requester after verification. I\'m dynamically crafting language-aware messages, ensuring they are clear about the permit status. I\'m including supervisor names, incorporating relevant details, and ensuring that all updates are complete.\n\n\n**Finalizing Permit Activation**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `handleSupervisorCloseVerify` function, focusing on the final permit activation. I\'m dynamically crafting an audit log entry that captures the supervisor\'s name, the date of activation, and their comments. I\'ve integrated alerts to verify that the field verification has been completed. The system is updating the current active permit, and I\'m ensuring all information is correctly saved. I\'ve finished the updates.\n\n\n**Finalizing Audit Trail**\n\nI\'m now implementing the final logic for `handleSupervisorCloseVerify`. I\'m including an audit log entry that captures details of the supervisor\'s name, date, comments, and permit status. I\'m verifying the system. I am finishing the system updates.\n\n```\n```\n\n**Finalizing Archive Operations**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `handleFinalClose` handler, focusing on archiving the permit. I\'m dynamically creating audit log entries. I\'m sending an alert if the site is clear. The key is confirming that all workers cleared the site, equipment has been cleaned, and energy locks dismantled. I\'m verifying the system updates.\n\n\n**Completing Archive Logic**\n\nI\'m now completing the `handleFinalClose` handler and the permit archiving. I\'m dynamically creating the audit log entry capturing key details like the final supervisor\'s comments, and date, including the final status. I\'m dispatching notifications to all workers, and validating that the appropriate site clearing alerts are sent, and site clearance information is entered. I\'ve finished the updates.\n\n\n**Verifying File Replacement**\n\nI\'m now verifying the exact file content lines 98 to 371 in `src/components/PermitDetail.tsx` to get precise substring end markers. The end marker for line 371 is the beginning of the `handleFinalClose` implementation. I\'m focusing on ensuring accuracy before applying any changes to the existing logic.\n\n\n**Finalizing Code Verification**\n\nI\'m now verifying the file replacement within `src/components/PermitDetail.tsx`. I\'m confirming the precise substring from lines 98 to 371 before completing my work. I\'ve finished the audit trail.\n\n\n"
